node.text:
Campers! It’s our last day of CAMP JOY! 🏕

Today’s episode was shot last week before Hurricane Laura swirled toward western Louisiana. My thoughts are with my neighbors to the west and this episode is a little love letter to summer in Louisiana, as tumultuous and sweaty as it may be. 

On this last day of camp we’re making old school situpons (if you were a Girl Scout you know what I mean), ginger brew by @adambernbach and sausage po’ boys with my favorite 🌭 @eatseemore meats and veggies. 

Thank you for joining me at camp this summer! I can’t tell you how special it feels to see you craft and bake along with these episodes! ✨ CAMP JOY was created and shot by me, created and directed by @heywhitneya, and edited by @shiraankori. This small but mighty team of ladies worked all summer to make this great and we’re so thankful you came to camp each day! 💋 Be well and take good care.

node.title: CAMP JOY: Po' Boys and Goodbyes

node.text:
Hey Campers!  🎉 We've got those backpacks and suitcases packed and we're going... exactly nowhere. Today at camp is all about connecting with the people we love and miss - with technology and 🌮🌮. ⁣
⁣
We're gettin' Dad on the horn and making his famous Wilson family tacos and a batch of pecan chocolate cookies. Comfort food that we hope warms your belly, too!  ⁣
⁣
🏕CAMP JOY is created by me and my girl @heywhitneya. You'll find recipes and resources from today at camp on joythebaker.com.⁣
⁣
We so appreciate that you watch and enjoy this show. What's been your favorite thing about camp so far?

node.title: CAMP JOY: Not Leaving On A Jet Plane

Hey Campers! 🎉 Welcome to Day 3 of CAMP JOY!  ⁣
⁣
You know it’s a good day at camp when you get a care package from your parents! Today at camp we’re gettin’ and givin’. We’ll make S’mores Granola Bars, popcorn spice and daisy chain friendship bracelets (with an obligatory Delia’s catalog photo shoot)! ⁣
⁣
We may not be able to gather like we used to this summer, but we can still drop a little camp kindness to our friends. ⁣
⁣
🏕 CAMP JOY is created by me and my girl @heywhitneya. You’ll find recipes and resources for this episode on joythebaker.com

Welcome to Day 2 of CAMP JOY! 🎉⁣
⁣
Some days you feel like doing the most, but this is not that day. Today at camp we’re kicking back to let the sun brew our tea while we have ice cream for lunch. ⁣
⁣
Keep those backpacks packed, campers! 🏕 We’re on this summer journey together! 🍦💓 CAMP JOY is created by me and my girl @heywhitneya. You'll find recipes from this episode on joythebaker.com.

Hey Campers! 🎉 Welcome to your first day of CAMP JOY! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
CAMP JOY is a six-part series taking it back to old school camp days! This year we need nostalgic comforts more than ever. Let’s make friendship bracelets, build fires in the backyard, and have s’mores every night!  This week: Hollywoodland, featuring fire pits and peach cobbler.  This series is shot by me and produced and directed by @heywhitneya. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We’re so thrilled to share CAMP JOY with you! ✨ Find the peach cobbler recipe linked in the profile and tune in next week for Day 2 of camp!
My favorite bake of the year is these sweet lil’ Vanilla Bean Daisy Pan Dulces and I’ll leave them here as a daydream for all us. 🌼 🍞 Recipe linked in the profile like we do.

June 2021 was like:
A haircut and color, 🙏. Testing holiday recipes and shooting them with Emily. Breakfast and gossip with my favorite dad. Sydney putting up the Christmas tree. Lots of Pimm’s. I really like my boyfriend Will. Shooting the cover of Joy the Baker holiday magazine. Our last @thebakehousenola virtual class until the Fall. A cake baked by Bronwen and the ol’ Summer Bucket.

⁣
🥂, Friday.
